{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_1lichtenstein_ver02/data/sn83045462/00280601706/1938021701/0247.xml":{"full_text":"TO HIGHER LEVELS\nSo-Called Commodity Issues\nStage Brisk Advance\nWith Big Board.\n8\u00bb the Associated Press.\nNEW YORK. Feb 17\u2014Shares of\nthe so-calied commodity division ad\nvanced spiritedly on the Curb Ex\nchange today.\nThe movement, patterned after a\nrise on the big board, was based, ac\ncording to speculative opinion, on ex\npectations President Roosevelt would\nsoon amplify his recent comment on\ncommodity prices.\nLeaders included Aluminum Co. of\nAmerica, Aluminium, Ltd.; American\nPotash Chemical. Newmont and\nPepperell Manufacturing, with gains\nranging from 3 to around 7 points.\nAlso substantially higher at the be\nginning of the last hour were Gulf Oil,\nColt's Patent Firearms, Detroit Steel\nProducts, New Jersey Zinc, Niles\nBement-Ponri. Creole Petroleum and\nAxton-Fisher Tobacco \"A.'\u2019\nCURB BONDS\nDOMESTIC BONDS.\n_ High. Low. Noon.\nAla Power 412s 't>7 _ 7u ;0 To\nAm G E 5s M0U8 10, lo'. lo.\nArk P L 5s Toi Mh\u2019a P.Va }*;{'a\nAs El Ind 4'iS 6.5 _ -..>\u20192 ;>5la\nAs G E 4\u2018as '4i) _ \u2018MU I *J4\nAs G E 5s '50 118 \u2019-i'a ~T\u2019a\nAs G A E 512s ',7 :u'a .14 :i4'j\nBala Loco tis 5n _ ;i 70 71\nBell T C 5s 55 A 11:! 1 17 117\nCan Pac ns \u201847 loir, inn\u2019, j tt-i\nCain Pw A Lt 5s '50 87 87 87\nCent Hi P S 5s \u201908 G lit\u2019, 94\u2019,\nCentral Pw 5s 57 D in in in\nCent Pw A Lt 5s '50 80\u2019, 80\u2019, so\u2019.\nCent St El 5s '48 35 75 .\",5\nCent St El 5'as '.'.4 7,> 74\nCen St P A L 5'as *57 4o\u2019, 4**11. 4nn\nChi M A III 4'as '50 A ill 97 1*7\n.Chi Ry, 5s '71 cod 44 -i:,;2 4 1\nCities Svc 5s '5n 57'a .*7 57'a\nCities S Gs P hs '47 HU Uni lutr,\nClt S P A L 5s '58 54\u2019, 54\", 54\nClt S P A L 51 as \u201857 49\u2019, 49\u2019, 4:1\u2019,\nCo a P A L 5'as 'll* 49\u2019, 49', 49\u2019,\nCon G E L A P 7' *s 'll in.. 1 **51 1 1**5',\nCont, GAE 5s '58 A 08', no, n8!*\nEast G A F 4s 50 A 75 